## Problem
The generic `guidesMatch` handler in `api/meta/[...path].js` (line ~319) catches ALL `/guides/<slug>` paths that are not sound-like guides and returns the same title for all of them:

> **"Metal Drumming Guide | MetalForge"**

This means the high-priority budget guides (sitemap priority **0.95**) — the site's highest-priority content tier — serve the same SERP snippet regardless of slug:
- `/guides/budget-metal-drum-setup-500` → "Metal Drumming Guide"
- `/guides/budget-metal-drum-setup-1000` → "Metal Drumming Guide"
- `/guides/budget-metal-drum-setup-2000` → "Metal Drumming Guide"
- `/guides/intermediate-metal-drumming-guide` → "Metal Drumming Guide" (duplicate title)

This is a **title collision** at the top of the sitemap priority stack — four pages share the same `<title>`, which Google treats as thin content and collapses in SERP.

## Fix
**File:** `api/meta/[...path].js`

Add explicit handlers **before** the generic `guidesMatch` catch-all (so these are caught first). Adjust slugs to match actual filenames declared in the sitemap's guides list.

```javascript
// Budget guide — 00
if (path === '/guides/budget-metal-drum-setup-500') {
  return {
    title: `Budget Metal Drum Setup Under $500 — Full Guide | ${SITE_NAME}`,
    description: 'Complete guide to building a metal-ready drum kit for under 00. Best budget shells, cymbals, hardware, and pedals for beginner metal drummers.',
    type: 'article',
    url: `${BASE_URL}/guides/budget-metal-drum-setup-500`,
  };
}
// Budget guide — 000
if (path === '/guides/budget-metal-drum-setup-1000') {
  return {
    title: `Best Metal Drum Setup Under $1000 — Buyer's Guide | ${SITE_NAME}`,
    description: 'Step up your rig: best mid-range metal drum kits, cymbals, and double-kick pedals for under 000. Gear the pros recommend for serious beginners.',
    type: 'article',
    url: `${BASE_URL}/guides/budget-metal-drum-setup-1000`,
  };
}
// Budget guide — 000
if (path === '/guides/budget-metal-drum-setup-2000') {
  return {
    title: `Best Metal Drum Setup Under $2000 — Pro-Level Picks | ${SITE_NAME}`,
    description: 'Semi-pro metal kit for under 000: Tama, Pearl, DW shells, Meinl/Zildjian cymbals, Iron Cobra pedals. The sweet spot before endorsement-level gear.',
    type: 'article',
    url: `${BASE_URL}/guides/budget-metal-drum-setup-2000`,
  };
}
```

**Also verify** the slug names against actual sitemap entries in `api/sitemap.js` — adjust the `path ===` checks if slugs differ.

## Estimated organic uplift
These pages are at sitemap priority **0.95** (tied with `/tools/*`). Budget drum setup queries have high commercial intent and strong GSC potential. Fixing title collision alone can recover SERP CTR since Google will differentiate these pages rather than treating them as duplicates. Target queries: "budget metal drum setup 500", "best metal drums under 1000", "metal drum kit under 2000".

## Verify
1. `curl -s -A 'Googlebot' 'https://metalforge.io/api/meta/guides/budget-metal-drum-setup-500'` → "Budget Metal Drum Setup Under $500"
2. `curl -s -A 'Googlebot' 'https://metalforge.io/api/meta/guides/budget-metal-drum-setup-1000'` → "Best Metal Drum Setup Under $1000"
3. `curl -s -A 'Googlebot' 'https://metalforge.io/api/meta/guides/budget-metal-drum-setup-2000'` → "Best Metal Drum Setup Under $2000"
4. The generic `guidesMatch` catch-all still handles remaining `/guides/<slug>` paths
5. No duplicate `<title>` tags in `<head>` for these three pages

## Done
Each budget guide slug returns its own unique keyword-matched title/description. Title collision resolved.
